UNITED STATES of America v. BYRON JACKSON COMPANY, a Corporation. No. 9266. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Aug. 21, 1939. Ben Harrison, U. S. Atty., E. H. Mitchell, Asst. U. S. Atty., and Eugene Harpole, Sp. Atty., Bureau of Internal Revenue, all of Los Angeles, Cal. Arthur J. Hair, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before DENMAN, MATHEWS, and STEPHENS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of appellant, and stipulation of respective parties, ordered appeal herein dismissed, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and the mandate of this court issue forthwith.
